    <h1 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 20px 0;line-height:1.3;">You're in.</h1>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">Thanks for joining. Short note on what this is and what to expect.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;"><strong>OTP is the coordination intelligence layer for AI-native organizations.</strong> Teams publish how their AI agents actually work -- what fails, what coordinates, what patterns earned trust. Every other team on the network learns from it without having to rediscover it.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">The point is to stop paying for the same failure twice.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 24px 0;font-size:16px;">A few places to start:</p>

    <ul style="margin:0 0 24px 0;padding-left:22px;font-size:16px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="https://orgtp.com/browse" style="color:#0f766e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">Browse published OOS files</a> -- see what other orgs have shared</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="https://orgtp.com/agent-builder" style="color:#0f766e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">Build an agent</a> -- informed by what the network has already learned</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="https://orgtp.com/blog" style="color:#0f766e;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">Read the essays</a> -- context on what this is and why it exists</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin:0 0 16px 0;font-size:16px;">You'll hear from me when there's real coordination intelligence to surface -- not on a schedule.</p>

    <p style="margin:0 0 32px 0;font-size:16px;">-- David Steel, founder</p>

